# Mongoose Model Rules

## Scope
- All backend models live in `apps/api/models/*.model.ts`.
- Keep model exports and names stable because controllers and tests import them directly.

## Schema Conventions
- Export one Mongoose model per file.
- Keep `userId` as `ref: 'User'` on Product and Order documents.
- Keep statics on `schema.statics.*` and mirror them in static TypeScript types.

## Model Inventory
| File | Export | Key Feature |
|---|---|---|
| `apps/api/models/user.model.ts` | `UserModel` | Cart instance methods + static email/password helpers |
| `apps/api/models/product.model.ts` | `Product` | Product owned by user (`userId` ref) |
| `apps/api/models/order.model.ts` | `OrderModel` | `products[]` with `{ product, quantity }` and `userId` |
| `apps/api/models/token.model.ts` | `TokenModel` | Password reset token storage |
| `apps/api/models/node-mail.model.ts` | `NodeMailModel` | Welcome/reset email and JWT token helpers |
| `apps/api/models/profile.model.ts` | `ProfileModel` | User profile state including `twoFA` toggle |
| `apps/api/models/two-fa.model.ts` | `TwoFAModel` | Persisted MFA secret for TOTP verification |

## UserModel Static Methods
- `isValidEmail(email): boolean`
- `isPasswordLengthIsOk(password): boolean`
- `getUserByEmail(email): Promise<User | null>`
- `isUserExistByEmail(email): Promise<boolean>`

## UserModel Instance Methods
- `addToCart(product)`
- `deleteProductFromCart(productId)`
- `clearCart()`
- If adding new instance methods, update the document type usage accordingly.

## NodeMailModel Expectations
- `sendWelcomeEmail(email, name)`
- `sendResetPasswordEmail(email, link)`
- `createResetPasswordToken(email)`
- `verifyResetPasswordToken(token)`
- `getResetPasswordTokenLink(email, token?)`

## Population Pattern
- Cart reads should populate `cart.items.productId`.
- Orders should populate `products.product` before returning API order data or building invoices.

## Do Not
- Do not move cart mutation logic into controllers.
- Do not call `.save()` on `.lean()` results.
- Do not replace Mongoose query APIs with raw database calls in normal controller flows.
